title: Veganism is not a revolutionary cause: it's principled but moderate.
description: The subtitle could be: "Why I'm never working with Harrison Nathan (again)."  Many vegans feel more comfortable with a sort of edgy misrepresentation of veganism as "extreme", "liberating" and "revolutionary" —they're more comfortable with those lies and exaggerations than they are dealing with the cause being as moderate as it really is.  :-/  Lousy synopsis, I know: working from examples, I think I do a better of explaining what I'm on about in the video.
